sequenceDiagram
    participant browser
    participant server

    browser ->> server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa
    note right of browser: Received 304 opening html
    activate server
    server ->> browser: html
    deactivate server
    note left of server: Received css

     browser ->> server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
    note right of browser: Received 304 opening main css
    activate server
    server ->> browser: main.css
    deactivate server



    Note right of browser: The user navigates to the SPA URL

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa
    activate server
    server-->>browser: HTML document
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the css file
    deactivate server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/spa.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the JavaScript file
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser starts executing the JS code that fetches the JSON from the server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    server-->>browser: [{ "content": "SPA is cool", "date": "2023-11-01T..." }, ... ]
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser executes the callback function that renders the notes


    Note right of browser: The user types a note and clicks "Save"

    Note right of browser: The JS code intercepts the form submit,<br/>adds the new note to the local list,<br/>and rerenders the note list on the page.

    browser->>server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note_spa
    activate server
    Note left of server: The server saves the new note to the database
    server-->>browser: 201 Created (JSON message)



    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser receives confirmation via a callback,<br/>staying on the same page with no reload.



    Note right of browser: The user types a note and clicks "Save"

    Note right of browser: The JS code intercepts the 'submit' event,<br/>prevents the default form submission,<br/>and adds the note to the local list.

    browser->>server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note_spa
    activate server
    Note left of server: The server saves the note to the database
    server-->>browser: 200 OK (JSON: {"message":"note created"})
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The JS callback executes upon receiving 200 OK,<br/>confirming the save was successful.
